#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:0.4"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:0.5"
msgid "6. Aññātakaviññattisikkhāpada"
msgstr "6. The training rule on asking non-relations"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.211, pts-cs-bu-np6.1.1, pts-vp-en2.42, ms1V_1974
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: paṭṭo → paṭṭho (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto paṭṭo hoti dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan was skilled at teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.3"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro seṭṭhiputto yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "On one occasion the son of a prominent merchant approached Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.43
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ āyasmā upanando sakyaputto dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr "And Upananda instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.6"
msgid "Atha kho so seṭṭhiputto āyasmatā upanandena sakyaputtena dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Afterwards that merchant’s son said to Upananda:"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.7"
msgid "“vadeyyātha, bhante, yena attho."
msgstr "“Venerable, please tell me what you need."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.8"
msgid "Paṭibalā mayaṃ ayyassa dātuṃ yadidaṃ cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāran”ti."
msgstr "I’m able to give you robe-cloth, almsfood, a dwelling, and medicines.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.9"
msgid "“Sace me tvaṃ, āvuso, dātukāmosi, ito ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "“If you wish to give me something, then give me one of your robes.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.10"
msgid "“Amhākaṃ kho, bhante, kulaputtānaṃ kismiṃ viya ekasāṭakaṃ gantuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable, it’s shameful for the son of a good family to walk around in only one robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.11"
msgid "Āgamehi, bhante, yāva gharaṃ gacchāmi."
msgstr "Please wait until I get back home."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.12"
msgid "Gharaṃ gato ito vā ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ pahiṇissāmi ito vā sundarataran”ti."
msgstr "I’ll send you this robe or a better one.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_1975
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.13"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "A second time"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.14"
msgid "“sace me tvaṃ, āvuso, dātukāmosi ito ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.15"
msgid "Amhākaṃ kho bhante kulaputtānaṃ kismiṃ viya ekasāṭakaṃ gantuṃ, āgamehi, bhante yāva gharaṃ gacchāmi, gharaṃ gato ito vā ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ pahiṇissāmi ito vā sundarataranti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.16"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and a third time Upananda said"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.17"
msgid "“sace me tvaṃ, āvuso, dātukāmosi, ito ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "the same thing to that merchant’s son,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.18"
msgid "Amhākaṃ kho, bhante, kulaputtānaṃ kismiṃ viya ekasāṭakaṃ gantuṃ, āgamehi, bhante yāva gharaṃ gacchāmi, gharaṃ gato ito vā ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ pahiṇissāmi ito vā sundarataranti."
msgstr "and he got the same reply."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.44
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.19"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana tayā, āvuso, adātukāmena pavāritena yaṃ tvaṃ pavāretvā na desī”ti."
msgstr "He then said, “What’s the point of making an offer if you don’t want to give?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_1977
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.1.20"
msgid "Atha kho so seṭṭhiputto āyasmatā upanandena sakyaputtena nippīḷiyamāno ekaṃ sāṭakaṃ datvā agamāsi."
msgstr "Being pressured by Upananda, that merchant’s son gave him one of his robes and left."

#. REF: pts-cs-bu-np6.1.2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.1"
msgid "Manussā taṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "People asked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.2"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, ayyo, ekasāṭako āgacchasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Why, sir, are you walking around in only one robe?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.3"
msgid "Atha kho so seṭṭhiputto tesaṃ manussānaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "And he told them what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.4"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.5"
msgid "“mahicchā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā asantuṭṭhā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics have great desires; they are not content."

#. VAR: Nayimesaṃ sukarā dhammanimantanāpi kātuṃ → nayime sukarā dhamma­ni­manta­nāya kātuṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.6"
msgid "Nayimesaṃ sukarā dhammanimantanāpi kātuṃ."
msgstr "Even to make them an appropriate offer isn’t easy."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.7"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma seṭṭhiputtena dhammanimantanāya kayiramānāya sāṭakaṃ gahessantī”ti."
msgstr "How can they take his robe when the merchant’s son was making an appropriate offer?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_1978
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.8"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.9"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.10"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.11"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto seṭṭhiputtaṃ cīvaraṃ viññāpessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda ask the merchant’s son for a robe?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_1979
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.12"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.13"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, seṭṭhiputtaṃ cīvaraṃ viññāpesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you acted like this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.15"
msgid "“Ñātako te, upananda, aññātako”ti?"
msgstr "“Is he a relative of yours?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.16"
msgid "“Aññātako, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.17"
msgid "“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātakassa na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā."
msgstr "“Foolish man, people who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s right and what’s wrong."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.18"
msgid "Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātakaṃ seṭṭhiputtaṃ cīvaraṃ viññāpessasi."
msgstr "And still you asked the merchant’s son for a robe."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.45
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.19"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.20"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_1980
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.21"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk asks an unrelated layman or laywoman for robe-cloth, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_1981
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:1.2.22"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-vp-pli3.212, pts-cs-bu-np6.2, ms1V_1982
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū sāketā sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr "At that time, while traveling on the main road from Sāketa to Sāvatthī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.2"
msgid "Antarāmagge corā nikkhamitvā te bhikkhū acchindiṃsu."
msgstr "a number of monks were robbed by bandits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū—"
msgstr "Knowing"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.4"
msgid "“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpetun”ti,"
msgstr "that the Master had laid down this training rule"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.5"
msgid "kukkuccāyantā na viññāpesuṃ."
msgstr "and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not ask for robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.6"
msgid "Yathānaggāva sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhū abhivādenti."
msgstr "They walked naked to Sāvatthī and bowed down to the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.7"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The monks said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.8"
msgid "“sundarā kho ime, āvuso, ājīvakā ye ime bhikkhūsu abhivādentī”ti."
msgstr "“These Ājīvaka ascetics are good people, in that they bow down to the monks.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.9"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu—“na mayaṃ, āvuso, ājīvakā,"
msgstr "“We’re not Ājīvakas;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.10"
msgid "bhikkhū mayan”ti."
msgstr "we’re monks!”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.11"
msgid "Bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upāliṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "And the monks said to Venerable Upāli,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.12"
msgid "“iṅghāvuso upāli, ime anuyuñjāhī”ti."
msgstr "“Upāli, please examine them.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.13"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmatā upālinā anuyuñjiyamānā te bhikkhū etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The naked monks then told Upāli what had happened,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.14"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upāli te bhikkhū anuyuñjitvā bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "and he told the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.15"
msgid "“bhikkhū ime, āvuso."
msgstr "“They are monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.16"
msgid "Detha nesaṃ cīvarānī”ti."
msgstr "Give them robes.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.17"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.18"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.19"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū naggā āgacchissanti."
msgstr "“How can monks go naked?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.20"
msgid "Nanu nāma tiṇena vā paṇṇena vā paṭicchādetvā āgantabban”ti."
msgstr "Shouldn’t they have covered up with grass and leaves?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_1983
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.21"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.46
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.22"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.23"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, acchinnacīvarassa vā naṭṭhacīvarassa vā aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpetuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, if a monk’s robes are stolen or destroyed, I allow him to ask an unrelated lay person for robe-cloth."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.47
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.24"
msgid "Yaṃ āvāsaṃ paṭhamaṃ upagacchati, sace tattha hoti saṃghassa vihāracīvaraṃ vā uttarattharaṇaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā bhisicchavi vā, taṃ gahetvā pārupituṃ"
msgstr "At the first monastery where he arrives, if the Order has a monastery robe, a bed sheet, a floor cover, or a pillow case, he should take that and put it on, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.25"
msgid "‘labhitvā odahissāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘When I get a robe, I’ll return it.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.26"
msgid "No ce hoti saṃghassa vihāracīvaraṃ vā uttarattharaṇaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā bhisicchavi vā tiṇena vā paṇṇena vā paṭicchādetvā āgantabbaṃ;"
msgstr "If there’s none of these things, he should cover up with grass and leaves before going on."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.27"
msgid "na tveva naggena āgantabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should not go on while naked."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.28"
msgid "Yo āgaccheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.29"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

# NOTE: _Cīvara_ means both a finished robe and any cloth that can be used to make a robe. Thus I vary my translation depending on the context.
#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_1984
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.30"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātakaṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatāniṃ vā cīvaraṃ viññāpeyya, aññatra samayā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk asks an unrelated layman or laywoman for robe-cloth, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.31"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo—"
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.32"
msgid "acchinnacīvaro vā hoti bhikkhu naṭṭhacīvaro vā."
msgstr "his robes are stolen or his robes are destroyed.’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:2.33"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, pts-cs-bu-np6.3.1, ms1V_1985
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_1986
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.6"
msgid "Aññātako nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.7"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddho."
msgstr "anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_1987
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.8"
msgid "Gahapati nāma"
msgstr "A layman:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.9"
msgid "yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any man who lives in a house."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_1988
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.10"
msgid "Gahapatānī nāma"
msgstr "A laywoman:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.11"
msgid "yā kāci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any woman who lives in a house."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, pts-vp-pli3.213, pts-vp-en2.48, ms1V_1989
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.12"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Robe-cloth:"

# NOTE: The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see [](Mv.8.3.1).
# NOTE: This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (_sugata_) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see [](Kkh.94.4) and BMC I, pp.565-566.
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.13"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_1990
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.14"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.15"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_1991
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.16"
msgid "Acchinnacīvaro nāma"
msgstr "His robes are stolen:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.17"
msgid "bhikkhussa cīvaraṃ acchinnaṃ hoti rājūhi vā corehi vā dhuttehi vā, yehi kehici vā acchinnaṃ hoti."
msgstr "a monk’s robe is taken by kings, bandits, scoundrels, or anyone whomsoever."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_1992
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.18"
msgid "Naṭṭhacīvaro nāma"
msgstr "His robes are destroyed:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.1.19"
msgid "bhikkhussa cīvaraṃ agginā vā daḍḍhaṃ hoti, udakena vā vūḷhaṃ hoti, undūrehi vā upacikāhi vā khāyitaṃ hoti, paribhogajiṇṇaṃ vā hoti."
msgstr "a monk’s robe is burnt by fire, carried away by water, eaten by rats or termites, or worn through use."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc20, pts-cs-bu-np6.3.2, ms1V_1993
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.1"
msgid "Aññatra samayā viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "For the act of asking, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commit an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.2"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe-cloth, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.3"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe-cloth should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#23-#29), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.6"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ aññātakaṃ gahapatikaṃ, aññatra samayā viññāpitaṃ, nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe-cloth which I received after asking an unrelated lay person without an appropriate reason is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.7"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.8"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.9"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.2.10"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc21, pts-cs-bu-np6.3.3, ms1V_1994
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.3.1"
msgid "Aññātake aññātakasaññī aññatra samayā cīvaraṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the person is unrelated and the monk perceives them as unrelated, and he asks them for a robe-cloth, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.3.2"
msgid "Aññātake vematiko aññatra samayā cīvaraṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the person is unrelated, but the monk is unsure if they are, and he asks them for a robe-cloth, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.3.3"
msgid "Aññātake ñātakasaññī aññatra samayā cīvaraṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the person is unrelated, but the monk perceives them as related, and he asks them for a robe-cloth, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22, ms1V_1995
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.3.4"
msgid "Ñātake aññātakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the person is related, but the monk perceives them as unrelated, he commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.49
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.3.5"
msgid "Ñātake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the person is related, but the monk is unsure if they are, he commit an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.3.6"
msgid "Ñātake ñātakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If the person is related and the monk perceives them as related, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc23, pts-cs-bu-np6.3.4, ms1V_1996
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.3"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if he asks relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.4"
msgid "pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if he asks those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.5"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if he asks for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.6"
msgid "attano dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc24, ms1V_1997
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np6:3.4.9"
msgid "Aññātakaviññattisikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on asking non-relations, is finished."
